<% content_for :title, "Frequently Asked Questions" %>

<div class="space-y-6">
  <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-4">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 tracking-tight">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">Find answers to the most common questions about the BCTS Admissions system.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="space-y-4">
    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 border border-gray-100">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">How do I check my application status?</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">Log in to your account, and your current status will be displayed directly on the homepage/dashboard in the main application status card.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 border border-gray-100">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">How do I submit my teacher recommendations?</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">Provide the names and email addresses of your references (math, science, and English teachers) inside your dashboard, and they will receive instructions on how to upload recommendations directly.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 border border-gray-100">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Where can I upload my transcript?</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">You can request your school counselor to upload your official transcript through the counselor portal, or you can submit it through the applicant portal's designated upload area.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 border border-gray-100">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">How do I schedule an interview slot?</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">Once your application has been verified, available interview slots will become selectable on your dashboard. Please choose a slot that matches your preferred academy and schedule.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="pt-4 border-t border-gray-100 text-center">
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Still need help? Please reach out to the admissions office directly.</p>
  </div>
</div>
